The paper focuses on the application of deep learning frameworks for detecting and recognizing faces of cartoon characters, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed methods using various metrics, indicating the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
